 Jimmy Iovine says “fame has replaced great” in today's music https://www.nme.com/news/music/jimmy-iovine-says-fame-has-replaced-great-in-todays-music-3512512?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=jimmy-iovine-says-fame-has-replaced-great-in-todays-musicAnagricel Duran Tue, 10 Oct 2023 17:12:05 +0000 Music NewsNewsRapRock https://www.nme.com/?p=3512512 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-3.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Inductee Jimmy Iovine speaks onstage during the 37th Annual Rock &amp; Roll Hall of Fame Induction Ceremony at Microsoft Theater on November 05, 2022 in Los Angeles, California. (Photo by Kevin Mazur/Getty Images for The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame)" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-3.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-3-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-3-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-3-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-3-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-3-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> &quot;They used to make records for radio, but now it&#39;s TikTok. That&#39;s why all these pop records sound exactly the same&quot;</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/jimmy-iovine-says-fame-has-replaced-great-in-todays-music-3512512">Jimmy Iovine says “fame has replaced great” in today&#39;s music</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-3.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Inductee Jimmy Iovine speaks onstage during the 37th Annual Rock &amp; Roll Hall of Fame Induction Ceremony at Microsoft Theater on November 05, 2022 in Los Angeles, California. (Photo by Kevin Mazur/Getty Images for The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame)" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-3.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-3-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-3-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-3-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-3-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-3-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> Jimmy Iovine, an American entrepreneur and founder of Interscope Records, has explained that “fame has replaced great” in today&#39;s music.</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/music-interviews/interscope-apple-musics-jimmy-iovine-tells-make-big-music-industry-2270040">Interscope and Apple Music mega-mogul Jimmy Iovine tells YOU how to make it big in the music industry</a></strong></li></ul><p> In an interview with <a href="https://consequence.net/2023/10/jimmy-iovine-interview/2/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Consequence of Sound</em></a> , the mega-mogul opened up about today&#39;s music world and the use of AI. After being asked about his views on the use of AI in songwriting and production, Iovine said: “I&#39;m not saying it&#39;s good or bad, but I think AI is going to be massive in songwriting on many levels. One, on a very basic level, if somebody is stuck and you want to experiment and get an idea. Two, is that not everyone, but too many people today are making records for TikTok.”</p><p> He continued: “They used to make records for radio, but now it&#39;s TikTok. That&#39;s why all these pop records sound exactly the same. So if you&#39;re making records like that, making records with this formula, then you&#39;re going to start seeing big hits written and recorded with AI.” </p><figure id="attachment_3512540" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3512540" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3512540" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/jimmy-Iovine-and-Dr.-Dre-posing-4-1.jpg" alt="Dr. Dre and Jimmy Iovine attend a basketball game between Los Angeles Lakers and Memphis Grizzlies Round 1 Game 6 of the 2023 NBA Playoffs against Los Angeles Lakers at Crypto.com Arena on April 28, 2023 in Los Angeles, California. (Photo by Kevork Djansezian/Getty Images)" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/jimmy-Iovine-and-Dr.-Dre-posing-4-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/jimmy-Iovine-and-Dr.-Dre-posing-4-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/jimmy-Iovine-and-Dr.-Dre-posing-4-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/jimmy-Iovine-and-Dr.-Dre-posing-4-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/jimmy-Iovine-and-Dr.-Dre-posing-4-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/jimmy-Iovine-and-Dr.-Dre-posing-4-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3512540" class="wp-caption-text"> Dr. Dre and Jimmy Iovine attend a basketball game between Los Angeles Lakers and Memphis Grizzlies Round 1 Game 6 of the 2023 NBA Playoffs against Los Angeles Lakers at Crypto.com Arena on April 28, 2023 in Los Angeles, California. (Photo by Kevork Djansezian/Getty Images)</figcaption></figure><p> Iovine went on to clarify that he said “big hits” rather that “great hits” due to the use of a formula. He then shared his observation on the state of music today and explained that with streaming, AI, social media, and other new technological shifts, “fame has replaced great.”</p><p> “Artists are making so much money in so many different places, which is fantastic, but after they have a hit record, they can earn a lot of money on Instagram and all this stuff,” He said. “I feel that a lot of people, a lot of artists, not all, but a lot of artists are taking their foot off the gas in the record making category. And that&#39;s affecting the quality of the work. And I think you&#39;re seeing that in a lot of different genres right now.”</p><p> He then went on to share some of his favourite artists at the moment. “There&#39;re always great artists that come along, like <a href="/artist/kendrick-lamar">Kendrick Lamar</a> and <a href="/artists/billie-eilish">Billie Eilish</a> ,” Iovine said, adding the likes of <a href="/artists/olivia-rodrigo">Olivia Rodrigo</a> , <a href="/artists/lil-yachty">Lil Yachty</a> , <a href="/artists/inhaler">Inhaler</a> , <a href="/artists/playboi-carti">Playboi Carti</a> , and <a href="/artists/turnstile">Turnstile</a> . “They caught my attention,” he said of the Baltimore rock band, adding: “I like what they&#39;re doing. I think they got the right spirit and the right attitude.” </p><figure id="attachment_3512541" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3512541" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3512541" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-2.jpg" alt="Inductee Jimmy Iovine poses in the press room during the 37th Annual Rock &amp; Roll Hall of Fame Induction Ceremony at Microsoft Theater on November 05, 2022 in Los Angeles, California. (Photo by Emma McIntyre/Getty Images for The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame)" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-2.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-2-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-2-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-2-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-2-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Jimmy-Iovine-posing-2-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3512541" class="wp-caption-text"> Inductee Jimmy Iovine poses in the press room during the 37th Annual Rock &amp; Roll Hall of Fame Induction Ceremony at Microsoft Theater on November 05, 2022 in Los Angeles, California. (Photo by Emma McIntyre/Getty Images for The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame)</figcaption></figure><p> Iovine joins the growing number of artists who have spoken about the use of AI in recent months, with the topic dividing artists in recent months. Former <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/oasis">Oasis</a> frontman <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/liam-gallagher">Liam Gallagher</a> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/liam-gallagher-responds-to-lost-oasis-album-made-by-ai-3432480">openly praised an AI-generated Oasis album</a> as sounding “mega” and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/grimes">Grimes</a> confirmed that she <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grimes-gives-fans-permission-to-use-her-voice-on-songs-created-by-ai-3434810">permits fans to use her voice in their own AI projects</a> .</p><p> Meanwhile, others aren&#39;t so supportive of the concept, with <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/nick-cave">Nick Cave</a> labelling it <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/nick-cave-calls-chatgpt-and-ai-songwriting-a-grotesque-mockery-of-what-it-is-to-be-human-3381620">“a grotesque mockery of what it is to be human”</a> , and later stating that he wanted AI platforms like ChatGPT to <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/nick-cave-chatgpt-should-just-fuck-off-and-leave-songwriting-alone-3421859">“fuck off and leave songwriting alone”</a> .</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/jimmy-iovine-says-fame-has-replaced-great-in-todays-music-3512512">Jimmy Iovine says “fame has replaced great” in today&#39;s music</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
